<action name=SYS-WERRSTR(2)>SYS-WERRSTR(2)</action>                                     <action name=SYS-WERRSTR(2)>SYS-WERRSTR(2)</action>

NAME
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            werrstr - set the system error string

SYNOPSIS
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            include "sys.m"\;
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            sys := load Sys Sys->PATH\;

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            werrstr(s: string): int\;

DESCRIPTION
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            When a system call fails, it returns an error value (often
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            -1) and records a string describing the error in a
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            per-process location. The verb r in <action name=sys-print(2)>sys-print(2)</action> outputs the
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            error string. Werrstr sets the process's error string to s,
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            to allow a function in a module to mimic the error reporting
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            interface of a system call.

SEE ALSO
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            <action name=sys-intro(2)>sys-intro(2)</action>, <action name=sys-print(2)>sys-print(2)</action>

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                                Inferno Manual
